Introduced Version
SENATE BILL No. 223
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 22-4.1-24-2.
Synopsis: Workforce related programs. Requires a state provider to
include in an annual report concerning a workforce related program
information regarding the number of participants who participated in
another workforce related program after completing the program.
Requires, not later than November 1, 2026, the department of
workforce development to: (1) develop a plan to collect information
from participants in a workforce related program after completion of
the workforce related program to monitor outcomes for the
participants; and (2) submit a report describing the plan to the
legislative council.
Effective: Upon passage.
Buchanan
January 8, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Commerce and Technology.
