Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
SENATE BILL No. 223
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning labor
and safety.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 22-4.1-24-2, AS AMENDED BY P.L.213-2025,
2 SECTION 283, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
3 [EFFECTIVE UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 2. (a) A state provider shall
4 prepare a written report concerning:
5 (1) its workforce related programs annually; and
6 (2) a new workforce related program not later than thirty (30)
7 days after establishing the program.
8 (b) At a minimum, the following information must be provided in
9 an annual report for each program:
10 (1) A description of the program that includes an explanation of
11 how the program aligns with Indiana's workforce needs and
12 coordinates with existing workforce related programs.
13 (2) The amount of funding provided for the program and the
14 source or sources of the funding.
15 (3) The number of individuals participating in the program.
16 (4) Demographic information about the individuals participating
17 in the program, including:
2026 IN 223—LS 6987/DI 141

2
1 (A) the age or ages of the program participants; and
2 (B) the education attainment level of the program participants.
3 (5) The results of the program, including:
4 (A) the number of individuals completing the program;
5 (B) the number and types of degrees, certificates, credentials,
6 and certifications awarded, and whether the degrees,
7 certificates, credentials, and certifications are industry
8 recognized, if a degree, certificate, credential, or certification
9 is awarded at the completion of the program;
10 (C) the extent to which participants in the program obtained
11 employment, retained employment, or secured better
12 employment as the direct result of participating in or
13 completing the program, including the number of participants
14 placed at the completion of or departure from the program and
15 within one (1) year after program completion or departure;
16 (D) a description of the specific jobs that participants in the
17 program obtained or retained;
18 (E) the wages offered to and earned by the participants both
19 before and after participation in or completion of the program,
20 including the starting wages at placement of participants
21 completing the program; and
22 (F) the retention rates of participants who obtained
23 employment or secured better employment as the direct result
24 of participating in or completing the program; and
25 (G) the number of participants who participated in
26 another workforce related program after completing the
27 program.
28 (c) At a minimum, the report for a new workforce related program
29 must include the information described in subsection (b)(1) and (b)(2).
30 (d) A state provider shall provide a copy of a report described in
31 subsection (a) to the:
32 (1) governor;
33 (2) legislative council; and
34 (3) department.
35 An annual report must be submitted on or before October 1 for the
36 preceding state fiscal year. A report concerning a new workforce
37 related program must be submitted not later than thirty (30) days after
38 a state provider establishes the program. A report provided under this
39 subsection to the legislative council must be in an electronic format
40 under IC 5-14-6.
41 SECTION 2. [EFFECTIVE UPON PASSAGE] (a) As used in this
42 SECTION, "workforce related program" has the meaning set
2026 IN 223—LS 6987/DI 141

3
1 forth in IC 22-4.1-1-7(a).
2 (b) Not later than November 1, 2026, the department of
3 workforce development shall:
4 (1) develop a plan to collect information from participants in
5 a workforce related program after completion of the
6 workforce related program to monitor outcomes for the
7 participants, including the information described in
8 IC 22-4.1-24-2(b)(5)(C) through IC 22-4.1-24-2(b)(5)(G), as
9 added by this act; and
10 (2) submit, in an electronic format under IC 5-14-6, a report
11 describing the plan developed under subdivision (1) to the
12 legislative council.
13 (c) The department of workforce development shall allow a
14 participant to provide the information under subsection (b)(1)
15 anonymously.
16 (d) This SECTION expires January 1, 2027.
17 SECTION 3. An emergency is declared for this act.
